      "content": "The problem is, \"stakeholders\" is such a vague buzzword that a sharp reporter will immediately call it a dodge. If they follow up with, \"So you're saying the donor pressure didn't influence this decision at all?\", how do we answer that without lying about the influence, while still making sure the news cycle doesn't label the candidate as inconsistent or beholden to special interests?",
